ss=\"sc-42d8a745-1 cwJkjb\">Save</span></button></div></div></div><figure><div data-component=\"image-block\" class=\"sc-3b6b161a-0 gyQxwn\"><div data-testid=\"hero-image\" class=\"sc-4abb68ca-1 eOgpjw\"><img src=\"https://static.files.bbci.co.uk/bbcdotcom/web/20250409-091508-0ef9b7676-web-2.19.1-12/grey-placeholder.png\" class=\"sc-4abb68ca-0 itgEAh hide-when-no-script\"><img sizes=\"(min-width: 1280px) 50vw, (min-width: 1008px) 66vw, 96vw\" srcset=\"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/240/cpsprodpb/1D42/production/_121009470_powerstation_getty.png.webp 240w,https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/320/cpsprodpb/1D42/production/_121009470_powerstation_getty.png.webp 320w,https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/480/cpsprodpb/1D42/production/_121009470_powerstation_getty.png.webp 480w,https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/640/cpsprodpb/1D42/production/_121009470_powerstation_getty.png.webp 640w,https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/800/cpsprodpb/1D42/production/_121009470_powerstation_getty.png.webp 800w,https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/1024/cpsprodpb/1D42/production/_121009470_powerstation_getty.png.webp 1024w,https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/1536/cpsprodpb/1D42/production/_121009470_powerstation_getty.png.webp 1536w\" src=\"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/480/cpsprodpb/1D42/production/_121009470_powerstation_getty.png.webp\" loading=\"eager\" alt=\"Getty Images Power station, UK\" class=\"sc-4abb68ca-0 ldLcJe\"><span class=\"sc-4abb68ca-2 kkAKIJ\">Getty Images</span></div></div><div data-component=\"caption-block\" class=\"sc-3b6b161a-0 jvncPH\"><figcaption class=\"sc-1b6a1475-0 feHvAW\">Researchers say the UK has little room for nature due to development and agriculture</figcaption></div></figure><div data-component=\"text-block\" class=\"sc-3b6b161a-0 dEGcKf\"><p class=\"sc-9a00e533-0 hxuGS\"><b id=\"the-uk-is-one-of-the-world\'s-most-nature-depleted-countries---in-the-bottom-10%-globally-and-last-among-the-g7-group-of-nations,-new-data-shows.\" class=\"sc-d16436d-0 jpoiOL\">The UK is one of the world\'s most nature-depleted countries - in the bottom 10% globally and last among the G7 group of nations, new data shows. </b></p></div><div data-component=\"text-block\" class=\"sc-3b6b161a-0 dEGcKf\"><p class=\"sc-9a00e533-0 hxuGS\">It has an average of about half its biodiversity left, far below the global average of 75%, a study has found.</p></div><div data-component=\"text-block\" class=\"sc-3b6b161a-0 dEGcKf\"><p class=\"sc-9a00e533-0 hxuGS\">A figure of 90% is considered the \"safe limit\" to prevent the world from tipping into an \"ecological meltdown\", according to researchers.</p></div><div data-component=\"text-block\" class=\"sc-3b6b161a-0 dEGcKf\"><p class=\"sc-9a00e533-0 hxuGS\">The assessment was released ahead of a key UN biodiversity conference. </p></div><div data-component=\"text-block\" class=\"sc-3b6b161a-0 dEGcKf\"><p class=\"sc-9a00e533-0 hxuGS\">Biodiversity is the variety of all living things on Earth and how they fit together in the web of life, bringing oxygen, water, food and countless other benefits. </p></div><div data-testid=\"ad-unit\" data-component=\"ad-slot\" class=\"sc-cce5f0ff-0 Bitbe\"><div data-testid=\"dotcom-mid_1\" id=\"dotcom-mid_1\" class=\"dotcom-ad\"></div></div><div data-component=\"text-block\" class=\"sc-3b6b161a-0 dEGcKf\"><p class=\"sc-9a00e533-0 hxuGS\">Prof Andy Purvis, research leader at the Natural History Museum in London, said biodiversity is more than something beautiful to look at. </p></div><div data-component=\"text-block\" class=\"sc-3b6b161a-0 dEGcKf\"><p class=\"sc-9a00e533-0 hxuGS\">\"It\'s also what provides us with so many of our basic needs,\" he told BBC News. </p></div><div data-component=\"text-block\" class=\"sc-3b6b161a-0 dEGcKf\"><p class=\"sc-9a00e533-0 hxuGS\">\"It\'s the foundation of our society. We\'ve seen recently how disruptive it can be when supply chains break down - nature is at the base of our supply chains.\"</p></div><div data-component=\"unordered-list-block\" class=\"sc-3b6b161a-0 dHQIrb\"><ul class=\"sc-55252feb-0 chlSKL\"><li class=\"sc-734a601e-0 huNRXw\"><a target=\"_self\" href=\"https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/science-environment-58306288\" class=\"sc-f9178328-0 bGFWdi\">Talks resume on global plan to protect nature</a></li><li class=\"sc-734a601e-0 huNRXw\"><a target=\"_self\" href=\"https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/science-environment-54357899\" class=\"sc-f9178328-0 bGFWdi\">Biodiversity: Why the nature crisis matters, in five graphics</a></li><li class=\"sc-734a601e-0 huNRXw\"><a target=\"_self\" href=\"https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/science-environment-55893696\" class=\"sc-f9178328-0 bGFWdi\">Prosperity comes at \'devastating\' cost to nature </a></li></ul></div><figure><div data-component=\"image-block\" class=\"sc-3b6b161a-0 hoQmHM\"><div data-testid=\"image\" class=\"sc-4abb68ca-1 eOgpjw\"><img src=\"https://static.files.bbci.co.uk/bbcdotcom/web/20250409-091508-0ef9b7676-web-2.19.1-12/grey-placeholder.png\" class=\"sc-4abb68ca-0 itgEAh hide-when-no-script\"><img sizes=\"(min-width: 1280px) 50vw, (min-width: 1008px) 66vw, 96vw\" srcset=\"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/240/cpsprodpb/1823C/production/_116767889_gettyimages-1164561722_amazonbasin.jpg.webp 240w,https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/320/cpsprodpb/1823C/production/_116767889_gettyimages-1164561722_amazonbasin.jpg.webp 320w,https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/480/cpsprodpb/1823C/production/_116767889_gettyimages-1164561722_amazonbasin.jpg.webp 480w,https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/640/cpsprodpb/1823C/production/_116767889_gettyimages-1164561722_amazonbasin.jpg.webp 640w,https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/800/cpsprodpb/1823C/production/_116767889_gettyimages-1164561722_amazonbasin.jpg.webp 800w,https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/1024/cpsprodpb/1823C/production/_116767889_gettyimages-1164561722_amazonbasin.jpg.webp 1024w,https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/1536/cpsprodpb/1823C/production/_116767889_gettyimages-1164561722_amazonbasin.jpg.webp 1536w\" src=\"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/480/cpsprodpb/1823C/production/_116767889_gettyimages-1164561722_amazonbasin.jpg.webp\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"Getty Images Deforestation in the Amazon basin\" class=\"sc-4abb68ca-0 ldLcJe\"><span class=\"sc-4abb68ca-2 kkAKIJ\">Getty Images</span></div></div><div data-component=\"caption-block\" class=\"sc-3b6b161a-0 jvncPH\"><figcaption class=\"sc-1b6a1475-0 feHvAW\">Biodiversity is dwindling fast due to human pressures</figcaption></div></figure><div data-testid=\"ad-unit\" data-component=\"ad-slot\" class=\"sc-cce5f0ff-0 Bitbe\"><div data-testid=\"dotcom-mid_2\" id=\"dotcom-mid_2\" class=\"dotcom-ad\"></div></div><div data-component=\"text-block\" class=\"sc-3b6b161a-0 dEGcKf\"><p class=\"sc-9a00e533-0 hxuGS\">The <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://www.nhm.ac.uk/our-science/data/biodiversity-indicators.html\" class=\"sc-f9178328-0 bGFWdi\">new tool</a> uses the Biodiversity Intactness Index to estimate the percentage of natural biodiversity that remains across the world and in individual countries.</p></div><div data-component=\"text-block\" class=\"sc-3b6b161a-0 dEGcKf\"><p class=\"sc-9a00e533-0 hxuGS\">The UK\'s low position in the league table is linked to the industrial revolution, which transformed the landscape, the researchers said.</p></div><div data-component=\"text-block\" class=\"sc-3b6b161a-0 dEGcKf\"><p class=\"sc-9a00e533-0 hxuGS\">The UK has seen relatively stable biodiversity levels over recent years, albeit at a \"really low level,\" team researcher Dr Adriana De Palma explained in a news briefing.</p></div><div data-component=\"text-block\" class=\"sc-3b6b161a-0 dEGcKf\"><p class=\"sc-9a00e533-0 hxuGS\">The assessment was released on the eve of the UN Biodiversity Conference, COP 15, hosted by China, a mega-diverse country with nearly 10% of plant species and 14% of animals on Earth. </p></div><div data-component=\"text-block\" class=\"sc-3b6b161a-0 dEGcKf\"><p class=\"sc-9a00e533-0 hxuGS\">World leaders are attending week-long virtual talks seen as pivotal in raising ambition for slowing the loss of nature ahead of face-to-face talks in Kunming, China, in April next year and the climate conference in Glasgow at the end of the month.</p></div><div data-testid=\"ad-unit\" data-component=\"ad-slot\" class=\"sc-cce5f0ff-0 Bitbe\"><div data-testid=\"dotcom-mid_3\" id=\"dotcom-mid_3\" class=\"dotcom-ad\"></div></div><figure><div data-component=\"image-block\" class=\"sc-3b6b161a-0 dFZIgd\"><div data-testid=\"image\" class=\"sc-4abb68ca-1 eOgpjw\"><img src=\"https://static.files.bbci.co.uk/bbcdotcom/web/20250409-091508-0ef9b7676-web-2.19.1-12/grey-placeholder.png\" class=\"sc-4abb68ca-0 itgEAh hide-when-no-script\"><img sizes=\"(min-width: 1280px) 50vw, (min-width: 1008px) 66vw, 96vw\" srcset=\"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/240/cpsprodpb/168E6/production/_121009329_wwf_decline_gra640-nc.png.webp 240w,https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/320/cpsprodpb/168E6/production/_121009329_wwf_decline_gra640-nc.png.webp 320w,https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/480/cpsprodpb/168E6/production/_121009329_wwf_decline_gra640-nc.png.webp 480w,https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/640/cpsprodpb/168E6/production/_121009329_wwf_decline_gra640-nc.png.webp 640w,https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/800/cpsprodpb/168E6/production/_121009329_wwf_decline_gra640-nc.png.webp 800w,https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/1024/cpsprodpb/168E6/production/_121009329_wwf_decline_gra640-nc.png.webp 1024w,https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/1536/cpsprodpb/168E6/production/_121009329_wwf_decline_gra640-nc.png.webp 1536w\" src=\"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/480/cpsprodpb/168E6/production/_121009329_wwf_decline_gra640-nc.png.webp\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"Wildlife decline since 1970\" class=\"sc-4abb68ca-0 ldLcJe\"></div></div></figure><div data-component=\"text-block\" class=\"sc-3b6b161a-0 dEGcKf\"><p class=\"sc-9a00e533-0 hxuGS\"> Andrew Deutz, global policy lead of international conservation charity, the Nature Conservancy, said the gathering momentum behind nature had not come a moment too soon. </p></div><div data-component=\"text-block\" class=\"sc-3b6b161a-0 dEGcKf\"><p class=\"sc-9a00e533-0 hxuGS\">\"As with the accelerating climate emergency, what happens over the next year will - to a large extent - set humanity\'s course for the rest of the decade; and what happens this decade is likely to define our prospects for the rest of this century,\" he said.</p></div><div data-component=\"text-block\" class=\"sc-3b6b161a-0 dEGcKf\"><p class=\"sc-9a00e533-0 hxuGS\">At the summit in Kunming - taking place in a two-part format due to pandemic disruption - world leaders will negotiate a framework for protecting nature and species for the next decade.</p></div><div data-component=\"text-block\" class=\"sc-3b6b161a-0 dEGcKf\"><p class=\"sc-9a00e533-0 hxuGS\">The draft agreement aims to conserve at least 30% of the world\'s lands and oceans, and increase funding for the conservation of nature. </p></div><div data-testid=\"ad-unit\" data-component=\"ad-slot\" class=\"sc-cce5f0ff-0 Bitbe\"><div data-testid=\"dotcom-mid_4\" id=\"dotcom-mid_4\" class=\"dotcom-ad\"></div></div><div data-component=\"text-block\" class=\"sc-3b6b161a-0 dEGcKf\"><p class=\"sc-9a00e533-0 hxuGS\">But elements of the draft lack ambition, according to a <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://committees.parliament.uk/work/448/biodiversity-and-ecosystems/\" class=\"sc-f9178328-0 bGFWdi\">report</a> by MPs on the Environmental Audit Committee.</p></div><figure><div data-component=\"image-block\" class=\"sc-3b6b161a-0 dFZIgd\"><div data-testid=\"image\" class=\"sc-4abb68ca-1 eOgpjw\"><img src=\"https://static.files.bbci.co.uk/bbcdotcom/web/20250409-091508-0ef9b7676-web-2.19.1-12/grey-placeholder.png\" class=\"sc-4abb68ca-0 itgEAh hide-when-no-script\"><img sizes=\"(min-width: 1280px) 50vw, (min-width: 1008px) 66vw, 96vw\" srcset=\"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/240/cpsprodpb/0D3E/production/_121009330_species_extinction_640_v2-nc.png.webp 240w,https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/320/cpsprodpb/0D3E/production/_121009330_species_extinction_640_v2-nc.png.webp 320w,https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/480/cpsprodpb/0D3E/production/_121009330_species_extinction_640_v2-nc.png.webp 480w,https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/640/cpsprodpb/0D3E/production/_121009330_species_extinction_640_v2-nc.png.webp 640w,https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/800/cpsprodpb/0D3E/production/_121009330_species_extinction_640_v2-nc.png.webp 800w,https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/1024/cpsprodpb/0D3E/production/_121009330_species_extinction_640_v2-nc.png.webp 1024w,https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/1536/cpsprodpb/0D3E/production/_121009330_species_extinction_640_v2-nc.png.webp 1536w\" src=\"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/480/cpsprodpb/0D3E/production/_121009330_species_extinction_640_v2-nc.png.webp\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"graphic showing how one in four species of those assessed by the IUCN Red List are at risk of extinction, including 40% of amphibians and 14% of birds\" class=\"sc-4abb68ca-0 ldLcJe\"></div></div></figure><div data-component=\"text-block\" class=\"sc-3b6b161a-0 dEGcKf\"><p class=\"sc-9a00e533-0 hxuGS\">The global biodiversity framework replaces the plan for the last decade, which missed all 20 targets.</p></div><div data-component=\"text-block\" class=\"sc-3b6b161a-0 dEGcKf\"><p class=\"sc-9a00e533-0 hxuGS\"> \"To play our part, we need the UK to step up and turn our global promises into action at home, to show that we are not going to let another lost decade for nature slip past,\" said Beccy Speight, chief executive of the RSPB.</p></div><div data-component=\"text-block\" class=\"sc-3b6b161a-0 dEGcKf\"><p class=\"sc-9a00e533-0 hxuGS\">Biodiversity is declining faster than at any time in human history. Since 1970, there has been on average almost a 70% decline in the populations of mammals, birds, fish, reptiles and amphibians.</p></div><div data-testid=\"ad-unit\" data-component=\"ad-slot\" class=\"sc-cce5f0ff-0 Bitbe\"><div data-testid=\"dotcom-mid_5\" id=\"dotcom-mid_5\" class=\"dotcom-ad\"></div></div><div data-component=\"text-block\" class=\"sc-3b6b161a-0 dEGcKf\"><p class=\"sc-9a00e533-0 hxuGS\">It is thought that one million animal and plant species - almost a quarter of the global total - are threatened with extinction.</p></div><div data-component=\"text-block\" class=\"sc-3b6b161a-0 dEGcKf\"><p class=\"sc-9a00e533-0 hxuGS\">Follow Helen <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://twitter.com/hbriggs\" class=\"sc-f9178328-0 bGFWdi\">on Twitter.</a></p></div><div data-component=\"links-block\" class=\"sc-3b6b161a-0 dHQIrb\"><div class=\"sc-666b6d83-0 sc-c4fb5674-0 gMiqnK iuHqSH\"><div data-testid=\"links-grid\" class=\"sc-666b6d83-0 sc-c4fb5674-1 kIEICy bPCWIP\"><div data-testid=\"chester-card\" data-indexcard=\"true\" class=\"sc-225578b-0 btdqbl\"><div data-testid=\"anchor-inner-wrapper\"><a href=\"/news/science-environment-58306288\" data-testid=\"internal-link\" class=\"sc-8a623a54-0 hMvGwj\"><div data-testid=\"chester-article\" class=\"sc-bec5e5d2-0 eUcHmo\"><div class=\"sc-9d830f2a-1 dOyfhs\"><div class=\"sc-9d830f2a-0 eKWlJZ\"><h2 data-testid=\"card-headline\" class=\"sc-9d830f2a-3 fWzToZ\">Talks resume on global plan to protect nature</h2></div></div></div></a></div></div><div data-testid=\"chester-card\" data-indexcard=\"true\" class=\"sc-225578b-0 btdqbl\"><div data-testid=\"anchor-inner-wrapper\"><a href=\"/news/science-environment-57655098\" data-testid=\"internal-link\" class=\"sc-8a623a54-0 hMvGwj\"><div data-testid=\"chester-article\" class=\"sc-bec5e5d2-0 eUcHmo\"><div class=\"sc-9d830f2a-1 dOyfhs\"><div class=\"sc-9d830f2a-0 eKWlJZ\"><h2 data-testid=\"card-headline\" class=\"sc-9d830f2a-3 fWzToZ\">UK government\'s \'toothless policies\' fail nature</h2></div></div></div></a></div></div></div></div></div><div data-component=\"tags\" class=\"sc-3b6b161a-0 dHQIrb\"><div class=\"sc-6bf80075-0 kkfrXx\"><div data-testid=\"anchor-inner-wrapper\"><a href=\"/news/topics/c88kg9wjn36t\" data-testid=\"internal-link\" class=\"sc-57521d02-0 emeJAW\">Extinction</a></div><div data-testid=\"anchor-inner